## Limitations

The report is based on available online resources and may not encompass all aspects of neglect as a form of abuse. The definitions and legal interpretations of neglect can vary across different jurisdictions, which may affect the generalizability of the findings. Additionally, the data on the prevalence and impact of neglect is subject to reporting biases and may not fully capture the scope of the issue. Further research, including empirical studies, is necessary to deepen the understanding of neglect and its consequences.